# Flask Conventions

## Application factory

- Construct apps only via `create_app()` in `app/__init__.py`.
- Config selection uses `APP_ENV` / `FLASK_ENV` (`DevelopmentConfig` vs `ProductionConfig`).
- Extensions are initialized in `_init_extensions`; models imported there for metadata registration.

## Blueprints

| Blueprint | Module | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| auth | `app/auth` | Login/logout; no public registration |
| dashboard | `app/dashboard` | Home |
| mission | `app/mission` | Daily missions |
| study_plan | `app/study_plan` | List + wizard |
| analytics | `app/analytics` | Analytics views |
| settings | `app/settings` | Settings / backup |
| founder_dashboard | `app/founder/dashboard` | Founder OS executive dashboard (`/founder`, admin only) |

- Keep `url_prefix` stable unless a milestone explicitly changes routes.
- Protect authenticated views with `@login_required`.
- Use WTForms for POST bodies; rely on CSRF (enabled outside tests).

## Route shape

```python
@bp.route("...", methods=["GET", "POST"])
@login_required
def view():
    form = SomeForm()
    if form.validate_on_submit():
        result = SomeService.do_work(...)
        flash("...", "success")
        return redirect(url_for("..."))
    return render_template("feature/page.html", form=form, title="...")
```

## Do not

- Put SQLAlchemy queries with business rules inline when a service already owns that domain.
- Flash secrets or raw exception traces to end users.
- Register new blueprints without wiring them in `_register_blueprints`.
